In [[medicine]], a '''laboratory specimen''' is a [[biological specimen]] taken by [[sample (medicine)|sampling]], that is, gathered matter of a medical patient's tissue, fluid, or other material derived from the patient used for laboratory analysis to assist [[differential diagnosis]] or staging of a [[disease]] process. Common examples include [[throat]] swabs, [[sputum]], [[urine]], [[blood]], [[surgical drain]] fluids, and [[tissue biopsies]].

